CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 21, 1951, pg. 8 reads: "In The Bridal March - Radiant smiles are registered on the faces of theses lovely ladies who are summer brides...Mrs. Arthur Coles...Mrs. Coles' picture is a Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait two men, including groom Arthur Coles wearing light colored bow tie, and two women, including bride wearing sheer mid length veil with floral edge and long sleeved wedding gown with floral lace overlay, holding large bouquet of roses, gathered in interior with circular mirror and floral armchairs, possibly at 335 Brushton Avenue, Homewood, vertical version
